title: Mancato accesso a Microsoft mail = Thunderbird bloccato
content: Da un po' i tempo il collegamento al mio account xyz@outlook.it non avviene nel momento in cui apro Thunderbird ma dopo un po' di tempo e non so perché. Però, dal momento in cui appare il messaggio che trovate in allegato, ogni altra operazione è interdetta e non ho accesso agli altri account perché Thunderbird risulta completamente bloccato. Anche rispondendo al messaggio di errore il risultato non cambia: tutto bloccato. Di sicuro Microsoft qualcosa ha cambiato (La comunicazione di Microsoft è in allegato) ma il vostro software, dopo aver segnalato la mancata connessione, dovrebbe lasciare Thunderbird libero di operare. Grazie per il supporto Cordiali saluti

title: Firefox freezes on Windows 11
content:
Firefox has started freezing my computer for no reason. At first I thought it was MS trying to get me to reboot so they could install updates, but when I did a hard shutdown and restart, it wasn't. I couldn't use the mouse or keypad.

Nothing on the keyboard worked.

I have my keyboard plugged into a multi-usb adapter, so I tried unplugging it and plugging it into another usb slot, but that didn't work either.

This is an intermittent problem. FF will work fine for weeks or months, then suddenly, it does this.

I've switched to a new profile already, so that's not it.

Is this a new bug? Please don't answer me by suggesting I do things I've already done. TYVM

title: Arabic characters missing, but *only* Arabic
content:
My Firefox has apparently lost Unicode support for Arabic, but only for Arabic: Persian letters (which AFAIK use the same alphabet!) display just fine. The attached screenshots show the problem via Wiktionary excerpts. Note that while the Arabic text appears only as boxes, the Persian, Azerbaijani, Ottoman Turkish, etc. texts all work just fine. It's clearly not a problem with encoding more generally -- languages as rare as Old Persian, Avestan, and the IPA appear normally. For some reason it's only Arabic that's broken.

What's going on here? How can I fix it?

title: Video playback causing GPU crash
content:
For a while now every so often when watching youtube (mostly) firefox causes my PC to crash. Normally with video and audio dying and repeating the last second of sound over and over robotically until the PC restarts. Sometimes I can still hear audio playing fine but video has frozen and I can still click to pause and unpause a video until it eventually locks up 5-10 seconds later. Sometimes it is completely locked up straight away. Some other occasions I can move the mouse for a bit but the screen is frozen and my mouse drags along dead pixels. It appears to be something to do with the graphics card (nvidia Geforce RTX 4060) but it is only ever activated by watching video, it never happens when playing games with firefox open. It has happened in some instances outside of video or youtube but was just after a video or with one playing on the side. It is 95% due to watching youtube and if not, firefox is always open when it happens.

Firefox is up to date as well as nvidia drivers. I even tried re-installing drivers fresh by removing old ones and re-adding and nothing. It will be an issue that will go away for a week or two or more, and not happen for a long time, and then out of nowhere starts happening again. Sometimes immediately after restarting and re-watching the same video again within seconds. Multiple times in one hour in some cases. Then other times it doesn't happen for weeks, almost as if whenever I update drivers or firefox, thats when it happens more, then as time goes on it goes away.

Any help would be great.

Thanks.

title: Excessive log entries with snap package on Ubuntu 24.04
content:
My `dmesg` is flooded with entries that are the following:

184252.870968] audit: type=1400 audit(1727667776.986:1099): apparmor="DENIED" operation="symlink" class="file" profile="snap.firefox.firefox" name="/dev/char/195:254" pid=346183 comm="CanvasRenderer" requested_mask="c" denied_mask="c" fsuid=1000 ouid=1000 [185202.435844] audit: type=1400 audit(1727668726.504:1100): apparmor="DENIED" operation="symlink" class="file" profile="snap.firefox.firefox" name="/dev/char/195:255" pid=348784 comm="glxtest" requested_mask="c" denied_mask="c" fsuid=1000 ouid=1000


There was a previous (years old) thread with similar complaints, but a different AppArmor log. The resolution seems to be to sidestep snap, but my impression is that Canonical has made that harder and harder.

title: Pay wall and Registration Wall Pocket and Search Results
content:
Look, I love the pocket topics that show up for me to read, and I like your browser. But, for the love of all that is decent, how can I stop receiving search results and topics to read in new browser tabs that require me to spread my information to yet another database, or pay straight up to access.

Let me cut to the chase. I will not ever, ever, pay or register for any of these sites. So whatever income is generated by depending on me to do so will never, ever, come your way. How can I stop this waste of my time and productivity and further degradation of my privacy?
creator: NomadicSpirit4

title: Remove bookmarks and add-ons etc from a second computer
content: I have signed into my Firefox account on my parents computer in order to see my bookmarks & have saved passwords, etc easily found, signed into & used. Sync is off but after I sign out bookmarks & password still on this computer. I don't want to remove these bookmarks & passwords from my Firefox account on my home desktop or my phone - just from this one computer. Research I found say a Firefox account not for this "function" - but now that I've done it is there NO way to remove it & not have to start from scratch & thus lose all the saved data, extensions, etc.???
